history.text: The RT score does not surprise me.
Did you think it should be higher or lower?
I think it's about right. The movie isn't terrible but also isn't amazing.
I thought it should be higher, I really enjoyed it
I'm not a fan of Jen Aniston. Jim Carrey is okay.
I agree with the critic calling it treacly. The sweet gets too sweet and is then just gross and heavy handed.
I like Jim Carrey, but Morgan Freeman was who really won me over
He is consistently a pleasure to watch.
Do you normally watch comedy movies, or do you typically go for a different genre?
My favorite genre is horror, but comedy is a close second.
Comedy is my favorite, so maybe that is why I liked it more.
Possibly.
I loved Steve Carell in this.
Even if Evan was supposed to be an antagonist,i couldnt help but like him
I was caught off guard when he stole the dialogue, but he played his part well
He has good range.
What did you think about Lisa Ann Walter?
Not much depth, she was the sister who didn't like Bruce, right?
I believe so, she was Debbie Connelly
Jen Aniston plays the same girlfriend in every film. Always expecting a selfish lout to suddenly make a romantic gesture, like he's going to do a 180 overnight and be who she thinks she deserves
When her total effort in the relationship is to call him 'hun' a lot and whine to a sister or friend
I don't really blame her for thinking he was going to propose though, I might have thought the same thing if I were her
She should have known better given what we see of him.
I thought it was funny that he created an email for they prayers. It was a creative idea.
And a good plug for Yahoo, lol
I couldn't imagine if I got a yes to all of my prayers, that would be great
Yeah, but everyone getting a yes turned into chaos pretty quickly
Im sure that is what would really happen, but its still a fun thought
My favorite part of the end was the signs, literal signs he sees, before getting hit by a car
I thought it was a really creative idea that the director did well
The prayer beads in his hand was a step too far in the treacly direction, though, returning to that idea
I would agree with that. What did you think about Bruce praying for Grace to find a man to make her happy?
That was him illustrating that he finally Got It and was less of an ass.
